info.name: Dfc2Api
info.description: Interface de programmation applicative REST qui offre des services GET, POST, DELETE, PUT Ã  d'autres applications

request.description:
LOGIN user to API

Add in the body the JSON for identification.

Sample JSON in the body:
{
  "username": "my username",
  "password": "my password"
}

The response should be:
{
    "token": "token returned",
    "user": {
        "id": integer,
        "username": "string",
        "code": "string",
        "fullname": "string",
        "email": "string",
        "last_login": {
            "date": "datetime",
            "timezone_type": integer,
            "timezone": "string"
        },
        "raison_sociale": "string",
        "id_cli": integer,
        "no_cli": integer,
        "id_depot_cli": integer,
        "nom_depot_cli": "string",
        "roles": array,
        "cntx_valid": boolean
    }
}

Set ApiToken variable with token value of the response for using in other call.

Read one user

Add in the header the token for authorization of user. For using ApiToken variable.

The response should be:
{
    "email": "n.cartier@dfc2.biz",
    "fullname": "Nicolas Cartier",
    "username": "NICA",
    "code": "PERSO124"
}
